## Bowtie Structure Rules
The Bowtie diagram has two wings and a central hazard event:
- **hazard**: the source of potential harm (e.g. "stored energy in press")
- **top_event**: the loss of control / release of hazard (knot of the bowtie)
- **threats** (LEFT wing): causes/threats that lead to the top_event — these are root_causes
- **prevention_barriers**: barriers between each threat and the top_event (degraded = partially failed)
- **consequences** (RIGHT wing): outcomes that follow the top_event — these are immediate_causes
- **mitigation_barriers**: barriers between the top_event and each consequence
- Barrier types: PHYSICAL | PROCEDURAL | BEHAVIOURAL | MONITORING | RECOVERY

## Required JSON output format
```json
{
  "hazard": {
    "id": "hazard-1",
    "text": "<source of potential harm>",
    "category": "BOWTIE:HAZARD",
    "level": -1,
    "parent_id": null,
    "confidence": 1.0
  },
  "top_event": {
    "id": "top-1",
    "text": "<loss of control event — the knot>",
    "category": "BOWTIE:TOP_EVENT",
    "level": 0,
    "parent_id": "hazard-1",
    "confidence": 1.0
  },
  "threats": [
    {
      "id": "<uuid>",
      "text": "<threat / cause leading to top_event>",
      "category": "BOWTIE:THREAT",
      "level": 1,
      "parent_id": "top-1",
      "confidence": 0.0–1.0
    }
  ],
  "prevention_barriers": [
    {
      "id": "<uuid>",
      "text": "<barrier name>",
      "barrier_type": "PHYSICAL | PROCEDURAL | BEHAVIOURAL | MONITORING | RECOVERY",
      "degraded": false,
      "threat_id": "<id of the threat this barrier addresses>",
      "category": "BOWTIE:PREVENTION",
      "level": 1,
      "parent_id": "<threat id>",
      "confidence": 0.0–1.0
    }
  ],
  "consequences": [
    {
      "id": "<uuid>",
      "text": "<consequence / outcome following top_event>",
      "category": "BOWTIE:CONSEQUENCE",
      "level": 1,
      "parent_id": "top-1",
      "confidence": 0.0–1.0
    }
  ],
  "mitigation_barriers": [
    {
      "id": "<uuid>",
      "text": "<barrier name>",
      "barrier_type": "PHYSICAL | PROCEDURAL | BEHAVIOURAL | MONITORING | RECOVERY",
      "degraded": false,
      "consequence_id": "<id of the consequence this barrier mitigates>",
      "category": "BOWTIE:MITIGATION",
      "level": 1,
      "parent_id": "<consequence id>",
      "confidence": 0.0–1.0
    }
  ],
  "summary": "<2–3 sentences: hazard, top event, critical barrier failures, key recommendations>",
  "recommendations": [
    {
      "id": "<uuid>",
      "text": "<corrective action>",
      "priority": "high | medium | low",
      "category": "immediate | short_term | systemic",
      "cause_id": "<node id this action addresses>",
      "responsible": "<role or department>"
    }
  ]
}
```
Rules:
- Every threat must have at least one prevention_barrier.
- Every consequence must have at least one mitigation_barrier.
- degraded=true means the barrier existed but failed or was bypassed in this incident.
- All parent_id references must point to valid ids defined elsewhere in the response.
